image:image.image:title: State & County Parks - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Veteran’s Memorial Park Located on Route 590 and Scenic Drive in Lackawaxen, enjoy a walking trail, basketball court, tennis court, children’s playground, baseball fields and a pavilion for rentals. Reserve here.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: Child’s Park Open all year. Located on Silver Lake Road. Scenic 1.8 mile loop trail encircling the magnificent waterfalls, old mill site. Picnic tables, fireplaces and pit toilets. No camping or swimming.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: Stokes State Forest Open all year. Rt. 206, New Jersey, 10 miles south of Milford PA. Hiking on the Appalachian Trail, fishing, swimming, picnic tables, camping and cabins. Children’s playground. 15,482 acres accented by the tranquil Tillman’s Ravine.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: High Point State Park Open all year. Rt. 23 New Jersey. 14,056 acre park containing Point Monument, the highest point in New Jersey. Hiking on the Appalachian Trail, fishing, tent camping April through October. Picnic tables, fireplaces, flush toilets. (201) 875-4800

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: Minisink Battle Ground Near Rt. 97 at Minisink Ford. 57 acre county park at the site of a Revolutionary War battle. Historical and natural interpretation, walking trails and picnicking.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: Upper Delaware Scenic Recreational River Designated 10,1978 as part of the National Wild and Scenic River system, the river corridor runs 73 miles from Hancock, NY to Sparrowbush, NY. Canoeing, fishing and sightseeing. The river is managed by the National Park Service. (914) 252-3947.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: Promised Land State Park Parts open all year. Just off Rt. 84 near Greentown PA. 2,971 acres surrounded by 8,039 acres of State Forest. Promised Land Lake is 422 acres and Lower Lake is 173 acres. Camping, fishing, swimming, boating, hiking, biking. 450 acres available for hunting. (570) 676-3428.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks - Make it stand out
image:image.image:caption: Sunrise Park Sunrise Park is located behind the Township building at 169 Urban Road, Hawley, PA 18428. It's open from Sunrise to Sunset. Parking is available, but walking to the park is the only way to get to the pavilion/playground. Picnic tables and BBQs are available for use as well! You could also take a hike along the trail throughout the property.

image:image.image:title: State & County Parks
image:image.image:caption: Delaware Water Gap National Recreation Area Open all year. Located along Interstate 80 New Jersey, and Rt. 209 Pennsylvania. 200 miles through scenic valleys, some areas available for biking. 25 miles of Appalachian Trail. Hiking, biking, boating, swimming and bird watching and areas for hunting.
